-- Morgan Stanley hires advisers from UBS
-- 
-- Mon Dec 6, 2010 3:39pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/12/06/us-morgan-stanley-idUSTRE6B559520101206

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Morgan Stanley Smith Barney has hired a four-person team from UBS managing over $1 billion of client assets. 

 Daniel Livingstone, Kevin Bednar, Lee Osman and Stephanie Hoffman joined Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ) Smith Barney's Madison Avenue, New York City office, according to filings with the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority. Livingstone, a 21-year UBS ( UBSN.VX ) ( UBS.N ) veteran, was ranked number 73 on Barron's list of New York's top 100 financial advisers this year. At UBS, the New York City-based team oversaw $1.1 billion of client assets, according to a source familiar with their business. (Reporting by Helen Kearney)